section.para:
API versioning is denoted by a version parameter(major and minor) in the URI. You are able to request a specific version of a resource by constructing the URI accordingly. For example;
rest/api/v1.1/students – request is made for version 1.1 of the student resource
rest/api/v1.0/students – request is made for version 1.0 of the student resource

listitem.para:
For teachers, the implied context is:
                            /teachers/{ID}/teacherSectionAssociations/sections. {ID}
                        represents the teacher's unique ID.

For parents, the implied context is:
                            /students/{ID}/studentSectionAssociations/sections. {ID}
                        represents their student's unique ID.

